  "verification": {
    "hash_rule": "For every record, compute sha256 of canonical JSON with keys sorted, MINUS the ots_receipts and hash_rule and ots_verify fields. Result should match the next record's prev_hash and the entry's `hash` in this manifest.",
    "chain_rule": "Each record's prev_hash equals the previous record's hash. Genesis (first record) has prev_hash='GENESIS'.",
    "timestamp_proof": [
      "Each record includes ots_receipts[] — one per OpenTimestamps calendar server contacted at publish time.",
      "Each receipt is a base64-encoded binary OTS timestamp file (~200-500 bytes).",
      "Base64-decode a receipt to a .ots file and run: `ots verify --digest <record.hash> receipt.ots`",
      "Within 1-24h after publish, the OTS receipt auto-upgrades to a full Bitcoin block proof. `ots upgrade receipt.ots` retrieves the current state.",
      "This anchors each record's hash in Bitcoin's proof-of-work chain — cannot be forged by the app, GitHub, or the calendar servers."
    ],
